result.execSummary:
The defendant Daniel Robert Rohde was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Lundell, RPR: Val Deiss, Clerk: Webb, ADA: Amber L. Hahn, DF ATTY: Alex Andrea, DF: Daniel Robert Rohde appeared.  Court called at 2:23 p.m.  Set for Motion Hearing. DE files a Plea Questionnaire Waiver of Rights Form with the Court.  Attorney Andrea recites the agreement.  State moves to amend Ct. 1 to a misdemeanor. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea.  Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads Guilty to the amended Ct 1 - 941.41(3G)(E) with the intent to deliver stricken.  DE pleads Guilty to Ct. 2.  Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE adjudicated guilty of  the amended Ct 1 & Ct 2.  Sentencing arguments. Crt orders:

S/W 2 years probation with conditions on each count to run concurrent
- AODA with follow through and any recommended treatment
- Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times while this case is ongoing. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.
- Court costs of $486.00
- Court grants the DE a payment plan and is to meet with the payment clerk
- DE eligible for expungment if there is successful completion of probation
- DE to report to probation today 05/06/15
- 20 days to appeal
